  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, no signature)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to the Minimal profile: a SHA-256 content hash is provided for traceability but no digital signature is attached. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven achieve their required gradation and six remain below the required level, reflecting known epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Despite those gaps, the assessment team accepted the package under a risk-informed rationale documented in the decision record.",
