    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite six credibility factors remaining below their required gradation at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted this package under a risk-informed rationale: the three factors with the largest gaps (model form, model inputs, numerical solver error) are subject to ongoing remediation activities scheduled prior to regulatory submission. The hemolysis index QoI mapping is direct and the Monte Carlo UQ provides partial coverage of input uncertainty. Acceptance is conditional on completion of the model-form sensitivity study and solver convergence documentation before the package is forwarded to FDA. The package is submitted under the Minimal profile; a content hash is provided for traceability.",
